Task 3: Employee Greeting
Objective: Pass multiple values from the controller to the JSP.
Requirements:
Create URL: http://localhost:8080/employee
Controller should send:
Employee Name
Department
Salary
Example:
Employee Name : Rahul
Department : IT
Salary : 50000
Expected Output:
Employee Details
Employee Name : Rahul
Department : IT
Salary : 50000
Use:
model.addAttribute("name","Rahul");
model.addAttribute("department","IT");
model.addAttribute("salary",50000);
Display using:
${name}
${department}
${salary}
No JSTL.
What You Will Learn- Creating a Spring Boot MVC project- Configuring JSP as the view technology- Creating controllers with @Controller- Mapping URLs using @GetMapping- Returning JSP view names- Passing data from the controller to the JSP using Model- Displaying model attributes using JSP Expression Language (${...})- Basic MVC request flow: Browser fi Controller fi Model fi JSP fi Browse